  "prompt": "What are some publicly listed solar companies in India?",
  "response": "India has several publicly listed companies in the solar energy sector. Some of these companies are involved in solar power generation, manufacturing solar panels, and providing other related services. Here are a few notable ones:\n\n1. **Adani Green Energy Limited** - A part of the Adani Group, this company focuses on renewable energy, including solar power projects.\n\n2. **Tata Power Solar** - A subsidiary of Tata Power, this company is one of India's largest integrated solar companies and engages in manufacturing solar cells and modules as well as providing EPC services.\n\n3. **Renew Power** - Although primarily known as a wind energy company, it also has significant solar energy operations and projects.\n\n4. **Azure Power** - Engages in developing and operating utility-scale and distributed solar projects.\n\n5. **Websol Energy System Limited** - Focuses on the manufacturing of high-quality solar cells and modules.\n\n6. **Vikram Solar Limited** - Involved in the manufacturing of photovoltaic (PV) modules and providing EPC services.\n\n7. **Kirloskar Electric Company Limited** - While primarily known for electrical products, the company is also involved in renewable energy solutions.\n\nThese companies are traded on the Indian stock exchanges like the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) and the National Stock Exchange (NSE). It's always a good idea to perform due diligence and check the latest financial disclosures and performance reports before making any investment decisions.",
